PractitionerCarnell Brame, Jr., AICP
Dallas-based Senior Planner at Desire Line LLC
Dallas, Texas, United States
Summary
I am a city planner based in Dallas (TX). I have over 8 years of
experience in community development, planning, and engagement
working within municipal government and have recently transitioned
to the private sector as a project manager. 
l hope to make Planning more accessible and strive to use my role to
create better communities for all. My focus on equity and inclusivity
permeates my approach to my work from start to finish. I am also a
big-picture thinker that is not fond of forgetting the details that take a
project or initiative from good to great. 
I have a Master's degree in City and Regional Planning from
the Georgia Tech Institute of Technology and a Bachelor's in
Science Degree in Urban and Regional Planning from East Carolina
University, with a minor in Architectural Technology Design. I also
have a background in engineering.
I joined the American Institute of Certified Planners (AICP) in 2019.

Desire Line LLC
